    "Let k be a finite extension of the rational number field Q.",
    "As in [Oht22, Oht23], we consider two types of algebraic extensions of k. One is of extensions of k obtained by adjoining the coordinates of certain points of semiabelian varieties over k. The other is of extensions obtained as the fixed subfields of an algebraic closure k by some automorphisms (in the study of the latter type of extensions, we allow k to be not only finite extensions of Q but also arbitrary finitely generated fields of characteristic zero).",
